lidating the governance entries to guarantee unique data during governance seeding. I'm focusing on \"Third-Party Agent Audit\" for \"Apex Global\" and \"Model Drift Check\" for \"Nova Energy\", ensuring the governance items are unique and associated with the correct client and project IDs. The seeding will only continue if the governance entry doesn't already exist.\n\n\n**Finalizing Governance Checks**\n\nI'm now completing the governance item seeding, ensuring data integrity by preventing duplicates. For \"Apex Global\" and \"Nova Energy\", I'm checking for existing governance entries and creating new items only if they don't already exist. The code now iterates through a structure, validating and creating new governance items to finalize the governance integration.\n\n\n**Finalizing Governance Implementation**\n\nI've completed the governance implementation, adding checks to ensure the governance items, like \"Third-Party Agent Audit\" and \"Model Drift Check,\" are unique and associated with the correct clients, verifying their presence before creation. I've also added system logging, to ensure these events are recorded.\n\n\n"}}
