{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:29:54.888Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Celebrating Seed Data Success**\n\nI'm thrilled! The linter gave it a clean bill of health. But even better, the seed data task is done! I've created a safe, local, idempotent, reset-capable seed script at `backend/app/seed.py`. The script has seeded representative, premium, enterprise-grade data.\n\n\n**Defining Data Set Elements**\n\nI've crafted a comprehensive data set! It features four client accounts with realistic names. I've built out four projects, four agent operations, four document metadata entries, four invoices, three support tickets, and three governance items. I've also set up pre-configured developer accounts with a secure local password.\n\n\n**Verifying Security and RBAC**\n\nI've ensured the backend security and RBAC test suite still passes. The seed data now includes more realistic role-based accounts. I've retained the legacy accounts for compatibility. The script is completely idempotent, with safe wiping via `--reset`. All is documented in `backend/README.md`. SQLite seeding was flawless!\n\n\n"}}
